Title: Transtherm Double Ermitage Glass Door Brushed Aluminum Fully Shelved
Body: The Transtherm Double Ermitage Glass Door Brushed Aluminum Fully Shelved Wine Cabinet combines 2 individual Ermitage cabinets side-by-side. Each unit has an independent temperature zone-perfect for storing wine on 1 side, and maintaining proper serving temperatures on the other.Two digital thermostats allow you to set and monitor your wine collection at the touch of a button. Its humidity control system not only reduces excess humidity, but also allows you to increase the humidity level by adding water to the system. The integrated heater element allows the wine cellar to be placed in extreme environments ranging from 32 to 95 F.Each side has 1 temperature zone that maintains perfect conditions from 43 to 64°F and 55%-80% RH for storing and chilling your wine collection.Each side comes with 14 adjustable rolling shelves (12 bottles per shelf) and 1 half shelf on the bottom. Using this configuration, the double wine cellar holds 364 bottles.Backed by a 5-year manufacturer's limited warranty on the compressor.Unlike most other cellars, Transtherm cellars are equipped for both cooling and heating - perfect for use in colder climates or regions with a wide variation in seasonal temperatures. This Double Ermitage includes rolling shelves in every slot.### Transtherm Technology* Silent Operation: Transtherm Ermitage wine cabinets operate at nearly imperceptible levels, emitting just 37 decibels.* Reinforced Insulation: The walls of the Transtherm Ermitage cabinets are made of three successive thermal barriers. The internal walls are made of strong and odorless insulating shock resistant polystyrene, which absorbs any vibrations from the compressor. The robust and aesthetically decorative exterior walls are reinforced at the corners by insulating sections. The 4. 5cm thick high density expanded foam which is injected, ensures optimal insulation. Transtherm cabinets thus have a rigidity adapted to wine bottle storage and thermal stability worthy of the best natural cellars.* Automatic Temperature Control: When the ambient temperature rises above the ideal wine conservation temperature, a cold circuit, driven by a very slow cycle compressor mounted on silent-blocks, automatically comes into action. The cold circuit coil, made of aluminum, is within the aluminum back wall of the cabinet, for a better temperature distribution. In the case of a drop of temperature, an electrical resistance, which is also within the back wall, will come into action and automatically increase the temperature.* Adapted Humidity: Bottle corks need specific hygrometric conditions in order not to dry out. The thermal pump (a Transtherm exclusive) allows hot humid air to be obtained automatically. Natural condensation on the back wall records a hygrometric value between 55% - 80%.* Natural Ventilation:In order to avoid the mold phenomenon, which would generate bad odors and risk deteriorating the corks, the Transtherm's Ermitage has natural permanent ventilation, based on the same principal as the thermal pump.* Absence of Vibrations: Choosing slow and balanced compressors, as well as disassociating them from the cabinet's body, allows the elimination of all residual vibrations.* Cabinets: The technical specifications used endow Transtherm Ermitage wine cabinets with perfect wine preservation conditions, follow the example of natural cellars. Your wine will improve for your optimum pleasure. The quality of the material, the display ergonomics and the contemporary design make Transtherm wine cabinets the ideal solution for safeguarding your precious collection.* Thermal Pump: The thermal pump process, (a Transtherm exclusive), by heating the condensed water, allows the introduction of humid air within the cabinet and considerably increases the hygrometry value between 55% - 80%. This principle gives the cabinet natural ventilation and constant air circulation.* Thermal Regulation: Transtherm Ermitage cabinets are equipped with an electronic temperature regulation system, specifically designed for this purpose. The sensitivity and precision of this regulation operates either the cold or hot circuit at the right moment, and as quickly as possible, in order to maintain, with an external temperature between 0 - 35C / 32 - 95F, a maximum temperature variation of 2-3F inside the wine cabinet. All Transtherm cabinets are equipped with a temperature setting and control panel, featuring a LED display.
Tags: Transtherm, Wine Cabinet, Wine Storage, Transtherm Wine Cellars, Wine Storage, Ermitage

Title: CellarPro 4200VSi 220V/50Hz Cooling Unit
Body: CellarPro's 4200VSi-220V 1/3 Ton Nominal cooling units are suitable for wine cellars up to 42 cubic meters in both commercial and residential wine cellars. The 42 cubic meter cellar size assumes that the cellar is constructed with insulation of R19 or better in all walls and ceiling (ie no glass or uninsulated concrete), the cooling unit is not ducted, a setpoint of 15°C inside the cellar and ambient temperatures up to 29°C outside the cellar.Performance testing shows that this unit maintains optimal cellar temperature and humidity conditions in extreme conditions up to 42°C more effectively than similar units from competing brands. 4200VSi-220V units also are significantly quieter than comparable units from other brands.This unit cannot be used in North America.

Title: CellarPro Air Handler Split System 8500 Outdoor
Body: **The CellarPro Air Handler 8500Sx** split refrigeration system is a wine cellar cooler designed to effectively and efficiently cool wine cellars up to 2500 cubic feet in size. Rated for external applications, this unit can be located outdoors in environments ranging from -20°F to 110°F including:* A compressor heater* Adjustable low-ambient fan control* Outdoor louvered grillsThis wine cellar cooling unit provides ducted refrigeration specifically designed to increase efficiency while minimizing noise pollution. The split system and ducted design allows the evaporator and condensing units to be removed from living areas, significantly reducing bothersome noise from the unit. The CellarPro Air Handler evaporator and condensing units both use variable- speed centrifugal fans with three settings, including a "high" setting for maximum performance and a "low" setting for super-quiet operation. CellarPro AH8500Sx Air Handler evaporators produce 51 decibels and the condensing units produce 57 decibels (ducted at the medium fan speed).The CellarPro Air Handler split refrigeration systems can be ducted up to 100 feet (50 feet per duct) and the evaporator and condensing units can be separated up to 100 feet apart. The split configuration allows the evaporator and condensing units to be located in separate locations and connected via a refrigerant line-set and power line. This allows for maximum flexibility when installing your CellarPro Air Handler 8500Sx wine cellar cooling unit. When NOT ducted, our evaporators and condensers require 12 inches of unobstructed space and approximately 600-700 CFM of ventilation when installed in a confined space.CellarPro's split configuration allows multiple ducting alternatives, as follows:* Collars or grills for EXHAUST (ie Supply) are located at the front (shown at left), top or rear of the cooling system, and are interchangeable to meet your specific requirement.* Collars or grills for INTAKE (ie Return) are located at each end (left: evaporator, and right: condenser), and include professional-grade air filters to protect the unit.The high-performance Air Handlers are designed to function in a wide range of temperatures from -20°F to 110°F. Exposure to temperatures below 40°F requires the [CellarPro Cold Temperature Compressor](http://www.vintagecellars.com/productview .as p?productsid=2101&prodcategoryid=204) ($99) and temperatures below 20°F require the low ambient temperature kit ($199).The price of the cooling system includes a bottle probe temperature sensor (10' cord) plus your choice of duct collars, indoor grills and blank plates.CellarPro Air Handler Split systems offer a choice of 110V / 60Hz wiring and power configurations:* Two plug-in power cords for the evaporator (5.7 amps / 15 amp circuit breaker) and the condensing unit (11.2 amps / 20 amp circuit breaker).* Two permanent power connections for the evaporator (3.6 amps / 15 amp circuit breaker) and the condensing unit (16.7 amps / 25 amp circuit breaker).* One permanent power connection for the entire system (25 amp circuit breaker). In this configuration, the condensing unit must be wired to the evaporator.CellarPro Air Handlers can be configured to include a factory-installed humidification system and a heating system for low ambient conditions (additional cost).**Important Notes:** For exposure to environments below 40°F, our compressor heater modification is required. For use in temperatures below 20°F, we recommend our low ambient kit.

Body: __Vintage Cellars Price Guarantees__ to beat any delivered prices on all Breezaire models! Call Now Toll Free 1.800.876.8789Breezaire is committed to producing wine cooling systems that satisfy the stringent requirements of collectors and wine enthusiasts. Breezaire wine cooling units can maintain the perfect aging environment in your wine cellar.The __Breezaire WKE6000__ provides excellent cooling for wine cellars up to 1500 cubic feet. Your wines will be kept at the perfect temperature consistently with a Breezaire WKE6000 cooling unit. The Breezaire WKE6000 uses the Sentinel II microprocessor control system. This system gives you a separate control panel with an LCD display, which can be mounted outside the cellar if desired. With the Breezaire WKE6000, you have a constant temperature readout and the option to connect to your home alarm system. The Sentinel II system also automatically controls fan speed for quiet, efficient cooling and runs built-in diagnostics to make sure you know about any problems. You also have the option to add a bottle probe temperature sensor which is highly recommended for warm locations.For smaller spaces, the Breezaire WKE4000 cools up to 1000cf. For larger spaces, the Breezaire WKE8000 cools up to 2000cf. Sizes are available for 650cf to 2000cf. We also carry the for the same quality cooling without advanced alarms and remote monitoring or the Breezaire WK6000, an economical option with the simplicity of a mechanical thermostat. If you need help choosing the right wine cooling unit, just call us at 1-800-876-8789 and our knowledgeable staff will assist you.

Title: HS 15000 High Static Split System
Body: The HS 15000 high static fully ducted wine cooling system is an efficient and quiet system designed to bring cooled and humidity controlled air into your cellar. Like other fully ducted systems, the HS 15000 cooling system keeps noise levels down by placing the noisy components of the system outside the wine cellar. The HS series is designed to function even in high temperature areas and can be ducted up to 25 feet from the cellar while maintaining static pressure. The HS 15000 high static wine cooling system includes a programmable temperature control and hi-lo alarms for peace of mind. It is rust-proof and low maintenance, and comes with the constant pressure expansion valve and solenoid valve standard. The motor of the HS 15000 is thermally protected for ideal performance in all conditions. All HS series systems are pressure tested and factory wired, but will still require a refrigeration professional for installation. The HS 15000 high static split system is designed for cellars up to 300cf and now includes a suction line accumulator.

Title: WhisperKOOL SC 2000i
Body: The WhisperKOOL SC 2000i wine cellar cooling unit is designed to effectively and efficiently cool properly insulated smaller wine cellars up to 350 cubic feet in size. As a direct replacement to the WhisperKOOL XLT 1600, the WhisperKOOL SC 2000i is the perfect solution for individuals seeking a reliable wine cellar cooling unit. Like the other models in the WhisperKOOL SC Series, the SC 2000i unit is built for quick and easy installation with through-the-wall installation technology and a single piece mounting bracket, eliminating the need for a support shelf. The SC 2000i is perfect for smaller wine cellars, such as the personal at- home custom wine cellar or small-scale commercial wine cellar. The improved performance and increased durability of the unit comes from its high-end components and all-new housing design. The new Condensation Reduction System increases unit efficiency and reduces electrical usage during operation. This unit has a 30°F temperature differential. In order to keep your cellar at 55°F, the area the unit exhausts into should not exceed 85°F. This makes interior installation ideal for SC series units.If you need assistance in finding the right WhisperKOOL SC Series Cooling System, call us at 1-800-876-8789 for expert advice. We also carry the full line of WhisperKOOL wine cooling systems.

Mix and match our components to create a system that fits your individual needs!This Redwood Tabletop is designed to be placed above the Redwood 6 Column Individual Half Height Wine Rack to provide a convenient area to open your bottles of wine. Title: Cash Register Stand Corner Display
Body: These modular components can be used to create a point-of-sale area that compliments the commercial wine display racking that we offer. Made from durable 3/4 inch plywood with attractive veneer, they can be arranged into a pod, cash wrap or even multiple lanes for fast and efficient checkout. The tops are made of cork for long life and stain resistance. Customized wine theme art images are available to make your store a unique experience for your customers. Comes in three easy to assemble sections. Sections Sold Separately. Cash Stand, Corner Display and Storage Unit. This Cash Register Stand Corner Display unit is utilized as the transition piece for the corners of your cash wrap. There is ample room to display a variety of impulse buy items such as liquor bottles, bottle tags, reading material, gift bags, and more. Title: N'FINITY PRO Double LX Wine Cellar (Stainless Steel Door)
Body: N'FINITY PRO Double LX Wine Cellar (Stainless Steel), a hybrid of the most sought-after wine cellar features in one complete unit. All the convenience of higher-end wine cellars at half the price.Our new line of N'FINITY Wine Cellars has the most sought-after wine cellar features in one complete unit. The LX model, holding up to 187 bottles, is a more spacious cabinet. Ideal for collections of varying bottle sizes. Its front venting allows for free-standing or built-in. And the innovative new shelf design maximizes your capacity while storing bottles of all shapes and sizes*NOTE: When we reference bottle capacity for our wine cellars, we are referring to the maximum quantity of "standard" Bordeaux-size bottles that will fit into that cellar. In reality, as you can see from the chart above, there is no true standard size bottle these days as bottles come in varying styles, sizes and shapes. Some are extremely tall and thin (like a Riesling bottle), others are shorter yet wide at the shoulders (like the Pinot Noir or Turley bottle) and others are tall, wide and broad at the shoulders (like your large California red bottle). If you have any of these non "standard" Bordeaux size bottles in your collection, your capacity can be lower than what we state the unit can hold.Here is our rule of thumb: If up to half of your collection consists of non-standard Bordeaux- size bottles, your maximum capacity may be reduced by 20- 25%. If your collection consists mostly of these larger sized bottles, your maximum capacity may be reduced by as much as 40%. The one thing we do know is that all collections are different, and that's the great thing about collecting wine! If you have any questions regarding your collection and its effect on your capacity, call one of our Wine Storage Specialists at 1-800-876-8789 for a full consultation.

Title: WineKeeper - Sonoma 8-Bottle (Mahogany)
Body: The WineKeeper Sonoma's handcrafted wood cabinet creates a tasting room atmosphere while maintaining the perfect temperature for your collection. The system maintains a temperature range of 42 - 48 F for white wine, and 46 - 68 F for red, using nitrogen to protect the wine from oxidation and spoiling. The cabinet requires a minimum vented air space of 1" on each side, 3" behind, and 12" above the unit.
SEO Title: 8-bottle Mahogany Sonoma WineKeeper | Wine Coolers & Display
SEO Description: The 8-bottle WineKeeper Sonoma wine preservation system in mahogany chills and dispenses multiple bottles of wine at once. Great for restaurants, bars and homes.

Title: Wine Guardian Split Wine Cellar Air Conditioner (model DS025)
Body: The new Ducted Split System (model DS025) is easy to carry to thanks to easy-to-grip handles and are both easy to install and versatile. The sleek new condensing unit design allows installers the ability to mount the system to a wall, balcony, or shelf as well as to a concrete pad on the ground. These units are ideal for owners of small to medium wine cellars who have no room for mechanical equipment or area for venting a self-contained unit.The 60Hz (DS025) has a BTU/H capacity up to 3,400 (@ 80°F inlet air) and comes with a Wine Guardian condensing unit with operating capacities from 0°F (-18°C) to 122°F (50°C).These new split cooling systems offer a variety of options. The evaporator section can be ordered with a heater, integrated humidifier, or configured as a serving-temperature system (with an adjustable, low-temperature cooling range of 42°F (5°C) to a high of 64°F (18°C). The condensing section comes standard in a low-ambient (cold weather) version, for installation where operating conditions fall below 60 degrees (condensing unit operating extends to a minimum of -0°F (-18°C).Initially there will be a 4-6 week lead time with the expectation to improve to one-week after reaching production volumes.
SEO Title: Wine Guardian Wine Cellar Cooling Unit - Ducted Split System (model DS025)
SEO Description: Wine Guardian is excited to introduce the New Ducted Split System (model DS025) designed and built to create a complete split cooling system that perfectly matches the evaporator and condenser sections.
